backend-ExportNotPossibleText.message: Como tienes activado el cifrado de extremo a extremo, tus contraseñas no se pueden añadir a la exportación automáticamente. Como alternativa, puedes utilizar la función de exportación de la aplicación para exportar tus datos.
backend-ExportNotPossibleText.description: Text of the notification when a user requested an export of the passwords app data trough the user migration app, but we can't export his data because it's end-to-end encrypted. The notification contains a link to the export feature in the app where the user can create an export manually.

frontend-PwDetailsEncryptionTitleSSE.message: Esta contraseña se envía al servidor a través de una conexión segura HTTPS y allí se cifra antes de almacenarse en la base de datos.
frontend-PwDetailsEncryptionTitleSSE.description: Info text for the encryption method in the password details sidebar if a server-side encryption method is used. The password sent plain text over HTTPS, then encrypted on the server before it's stored

frontend-PwDetailsEncryptionTitleCSE.message: Esta contraseña se cifra en tu dispositivo antes de ser enviada al servidor. Nadie puede leer esta contraseña sin conocer tu contraseña de cifrado.
frontend-PwDetailsEncryptionTitleCSE.description: Info text for the encryption method in the password details sidebar if a client side / end-to-end encryption method is used. The password is encrypted on the users device before it's sent to the server and can only be decrypted with the users encryption password

frontend-PasswordEncryptionCSE.description: Label for the client side / end-to-end encryption method

frontend-BrowserConsoleWarningLine1.description: First section of the warning message users see when they open the browser developer console which explains that the feature is intended for developers only

frontend-BrowserConsoleWarningLine2.message: Si alguien te dice que copies y pegues algo aquí, es probable que acceda a tus contraseñas o se apodere de tu cuenta.
frontend-BrowserConsoleWarningLine2.description: Second section of the warning message users see when they open the browser developer console which explains that pasting code here may give others access to their passwords and their account

frontend-BrowserConsoleWarningLine3.description: Third section of the warning message users see when they open the browser developer console which contains a link to the handbook page with more information

backend-SettingsEncryptionSection.description: Label of the encryption settings section in the app settings in the admin area

backend-SettingsEncryptionSSEv3.description: Label of the option to enable SSEv3 in the encryption settings section in the app settings in the admin area

backend-EOLNextcloudText2.message: Actualiza a Nextcloud $STR_1$ para futuras actualizaciones.

settings-WebauthnEncryptionPassphrase.description: Label of the password input for the user to enter their encryption passphrase in the WebAuthn setup dialog

settings-WebauthnEncryptionPassphraseTex.message: Introduzca su contraseña de cifrado a continuación. Se guardará en su navegador y la aplicación intentará utilizarla la próxima vez que la abra. Si la contraseña no es válida, el inicio de sesión fallará una vez y WebAuthn se desactivará.
settings-WebauthnEncryptionPassphraseTex.description: Explanation text in the WebAuthn setup dialog. The user must enter their encryption passphrase in the form below. The passphrase won't be checked, it will just be saved in the users browser. The app will attempt to log in with the password when opened. IF that is not possible/fails, WebAuthn will be disabled.

settings-WebauthnLoginSetupSuccess.message: WebAuthn ya está activado. La aplicación intentará utilizar la contraseña guardada la próxima vez que inicie sesión.

frontend-WebAuthnLoginDisabled.description: Notification message when the WebAuthn login was disabled due to the provided passphrase not working
